  "text": "The 43,739 eukaryotic sequences with an average sequence length of 434 bp were identified as 1414 OTUs by phylogenic analysis (Table S1 ). Moreover, 94.79%-98.66% of Good's coverages at the 97% similarity level indicated that the sequencing results were sufficient to represent the natural eukaryotic community [CITATION_1] . Rarefaction curve analysis also revealed that the overall eukaryotic diversity was well exhibited (Fig. S1) .",
